==== GTEX ADIPOSE

-- Prepare eQTL files from Adipose Gtex study for SMR by using MeCS (to join the two adipose types on Gtex accounting for sample overlap). 
    -- Make besd files from 
    "Note that the *.egenes.txt.gz files contain data for all genes tested"
    GTEx_Analysis_v7_eQTL.tar.gz
awk 'BEGIN { OFS = "\t"} { print $19, $14, $15, $16, $17, $22, $1, $3, $4, $2, $6, $28, $26, $27 }' Adipose_Subcutaneous.v7.egenes.txt > Adipose_Subcutaneous.v7.query.txt

grep '^rs' Adipose_Subcutaneous.v7.query.txt > Adipose_Subcutaneous.v7.query2.txt

/hpc/users/hemerd01/daiane/projects/smr/smr_Linux --qfile Adipose_Subcutaneous.v7.query.txt --make-besd --out mybesd Adipose_Subcutaneous.v7

    -- Make an adipose.list with gtex besd files
./smr_Linux --besd-flist /hpc/users/hemerd01/daiane/projects/smr/data/eqtl/adipose.list --mecs --thread-num 5 --out /hpc/users/hemerd01/daiane/projects/smr/data/eqtl/gtex_adipose2
    
STATUS: making besd files from Adrenal_Gland.v7.egenes.txt.gz did not work. Jian says "Ting (cced) reminded me that we need “null SNPs” (p < 0.01) to estimate sample overlap between two data sets. However, in your data, you filtered out all the SNPs with p > 1e-5, which caused the error.", so maybe it's needed to download the big Gtex file and filter it by p<0.01 in order to generate besd files that work for MeCS.
DECISION: to run SMR in each Adipose tissue separately for now.


